Peru Stocks: Alicorp, Atacocha, Buenaventura, Siderperu

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-09-12T20:53:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/peru-stocks-alicorp-atacocha-buenaventura-siderperu.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rose 0.2 percent to 19,939.77. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 0.3 percent to 2,632.78.  Industrial stocks gained as investors bet the U.S.
government will find a solution to reactivate the economy, Jose Luis Bustamante, head of trading at Cartisa SAB, said in a
telephone interview.  Alicorp SA (ALICORC1)  (ALICORC1 PE), Peru’s largest foodstuff maker,
rose 4.6 percent to 5.70 soles after HSBC analyst Pedro Herrera
rated the stock a new “overweight.”  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE),
Peru’s largest sugar producer and a unit of Gloria SA, climbed
2.1 percent to 14.40 soles after futures advanced in New York.
 Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau
SA known as Siderperu, gained 1.7 percent to 1.20 soles.  Copper, gold and silver miners fell after futures declined
in New York and London  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, dropped 2.4 percent to 41 cents. Cia. de
Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest precious-
metals miner, fell 1.1 percent to $45.50. Cia. Minera Atacocha
SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based silver and zinc mining company,
declined 1 percent to 1 sol.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  